  "book": "discrete-math",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Key Concepts"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "A **set** is an unordered collection of distinct elements.",
        "**Set notation**: roster $\\{1, 2, 3\\}$ or set-builder \n $\\setbuild{x}{P(x)}$.",
        "$A \\subseteq B$ means $A$ is a **subset** of $B$.",
        "The **power set** $\\powerset(A)$ contains all subsets of $A$; \n if $\\card{A} = n$, then $\\card{\\powerset(A)} = 2^n$.",
        "**Set operations**: union ($\\cup$), intersection ($\\cap$), \n difference ($-$), complement ($\\comp{A}$), Cartesian product ($\\times$).",
        "**De Morgan's Laws**: $\\comp{(A \\cup B)} = \\comp{A} \\cap \\comp{B}$ \n and $\\comp{(A \\cap B)} = \\comp{A} \\cup \\comp{B}$.",
        "A **function** $f: A \\to B$ assigns each $a \\in A$ exactly \n one $b \\in B$.",
        "**Injective**: different inputs give different outputs.",
        "**Surjective**: every element in the codomain is an output.",
        "**Bijective**: both injective and surjective; has an inverse.",
        "**Sequences** are functions from integers to a set; \n **summations** $\\sum$ and **products** $\\prod$ provide \n compact notation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Important Formulas"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "**Formula**",
        "**Description**"
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "$\\card{A \\cup B} = \\card{A} + \\card{B} - \\card{A \\cap B}$",
          "Inclusion-Exclusion"
        ],
        [
          "$\\card{A \\times B} = \\card{A} \\cdot \\card{B}$",
          "Cartesian product size"
        ],
        [
          "$\\displaystyle\\sum_{i=1}^{n} i = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2}$",
          "Sum of first $n$ integers"
        ],
        [
          "$\\displaystyle\\sum_{i=0}^{n} r^i = \\frac{r^{n+1} - 1}{r - 1}$",
          "Geometric sum"
        ]
      ],
      "alignment": [
        "left",
        "left"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Review Exercises"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Let $A = \\{1, 2, 3, 4\\}$, $B = \\{3, 4, 5, 6\\}$, $C = \\{4, 5, 6, 7\\}$. \nFind:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$A \\cup B \\cup C$",
        "$A \\cap B \\cap C$",
        "$(A \\cup B) \\cap C$",
        "$A - (B \\cup C)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Let $A = \\{a, b\\}$ and $B = \\{1, 2, 3\\}$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "List all elements of $\\powerset(A)$.",
        "How many functions are there from $A$ to $B$?",
        "How many injective functions from $A$ to $B$?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For each function $f: \\R \\to \\R$, determine if it is injective, \nsurjective, bijective, or none:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$f(x) = 3x - 7$",
        "$f(x) = x^2 - 4x$",
        "$f(x) = x^3 + 1$",
        "$f(x) = \\sin x$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If $f(x) = 2x + 1$ and $g(x) = x^2$, find:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$(f \\circ g)(3)$",
        "$(g \\circ f)(3)$",
        "$(f \\circ g)(x)$",
        "$f^{-1}(x)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\displaystyle\\sum_{k=1}^{100} k$",
        "$\\displaystyle\\sum_{i=0}^{10} 2^i$",
        "$\\displaystyle\\prod_{j=1}^{6} j$"
      ]
    }
  ]
